            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hello *,\n\nI have tried out the Zend Framework, in special the Feed functions.\n\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Feed.php';\n$rssdata = Zend_Feed::import('http:\/\/www.computerpartner.de\/rss\/news.xml');\nforeach ( $rssdata as $item ) {\n        print \"Title: \".$item->title().\"\\n\";\n}\n\nWhat you see the umlaute are crappy. Exp for an \"\u00fc\" you see \"\u00c3\u00bc\". and so on.\nI don't know where to dix it - maybe someone find the bug. ;-)\n\nCheers\n"
